I had previously made some stencils with laminated paper and used those for a decent enough finish on the case. As a bonus, I also made a t-shirt with the kolibri logo, using those same materials with a shirt and bleach in a spray bottle. Nice!

## Conclusion

The PC is amazingly quiet. In fact much quieter than the old annoying water cooled PC ever was. Temps are well within acceptable ranges when gaming, and maybe one day I'll have an overclockable CPU to test it at its limits.

The PC mod was quite simple and didn't take too much time, but still I feel like I really made this computer my own. The look is subjectively nice and I love it. And no over the counter pre-built can ever compete with that!

